SIMPLE: submissive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Submissive
<hw>Sub*mis"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Inclined or ready to submit; acknowledging one's inferiority;
yielding; obedient; humble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not at his feet <qex>submissive</qex> in distress,⟦br⟧
Creature so fair his reconcilement seeking.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Showing a readiness to submit; expressing
submission; <as>as, a <ex>submissive</ex> demeanor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With a <qex>submissive</qex> step I hasted down.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Obedient; compliant; yielding; obsequious;
subservient; humble; modest; passive.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sub*mis"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sub*mis"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Submissly</ent>⟦br⟧
